	('7cde251b-be14-429b-9d8d-5cf1bd1fc4c9', '95364f0d-23fb-4616-b0f4-48caafee5439', 'What jobs match my skills and experience?', '[{"id": "ebcf6bbe-4495-4c28-8810-de8260edcd2f", "role": "user", "content": "What jobs match my skills and experience?", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T07:03:18.455Z"}, {"id": "2ea91370-c47f-4d43-bd67-00f1380bf646", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay Gokul, since you''re studying B.COM at PES University, there are a bunch of career paths that could be a great fit. Many B.COM grads find success in roles like:\n\n*   **Accounting and Finance:** Think roles like Accountant, Financial Analyst, or Tax Consultant. These often require strong analytical and numerical skills.\n*   **Banking:** Opportunities exist as Bank Teller, Loan Officer, or even moving into management roles.\n*   **Business Development:** Roles like Sales Executive or Business Development Manager could be a good fit if you enjoy networking and building relationships.\n*   **Marketing:** With some additional skills, you could explore roles in marketing, market research, or advertising.\n\nTo give you more specific recommendations, tell me a bit more about:\n\n*   **Any internships or work experience you''ve had:** Even seemingly small experiences can be relevant.\n*   **Specific skills you''ve developed:** Think about software you''re proficient in (like Excel), communication skills, or any specific knowledge areas.\n*   **What you enjoy:** What subjects in your B.COM program do you find most interesting? What kind of work environment do you prefer?\n\nOnce I have a better understanding of your background and interests, I can give you more tailored advice.\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T07:03:18.455Z"}]', '2026-01-29 07:03:18.469643+00', '2026-01-29 07:03:18.469643+00'),
	('ef21ad45-5640-4f3f-9f81-8526afebc01a', '95364f0d-23fb-4616-b0f4-48caafee5439', 'What jobs match my skills and experience?', '[{"id": "29c6109f-e924-49fb-8918-670360b59fd4", "role": "user", "content": "What jobs match my skills and experience?", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T07:28:53.745Z"}, {"id": "56015ec2-ac01-4a26-a8f6-51d737a7fe84", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay Gokul, since you''re studying B.COM at PES University, let''s explore some job options that typically align well with your field. To give you the *most* relevant suggestions, I need a little more information about your specific skills and experiences. However, here are some common paths for B.COM graduates, along with the kinds of skills and experiences that make you a strong candidate:\n\n**1. Finance Roles:**\n\n*   **Common roles:** Financial Analyst, Accountant, Auditor, Banking Associate\n*   **Relevant Skills:** Financial accounting, data analysis, problem-solving, attention to detail, strong math skills, understanding of financial regulations.\n*   **Helpful Experiences:** Internships in finance departments, accounting firms, banks; projects involving financial modeling or analysis; relevant coursework.\n\n**2. Accounting Roles:**\n\n*   **Common roles:** Accountant, Tax Accountant, Auditor, Bookkeeper\n*   **Relevant Skills:** Financial accounting, taxation, auditing, attention to detail, proficiency in accounting software (e.g., Tally, SAP).\n*   **Helpful Experiences:** Internships in accounting firms or company accounting departments, volunteer tax preparation, coursework in accounting principles.\n\n**3. Business and Management Roles:**\n\n*   **Common roles:** Business Development Associate, Marketing Associate, Sales Associate, Operations Analyst, Management Trainee.\n*   **Relevant Skills:** Communication, teamwork, leadership, problem-solving, analytical skills, understanding of business principles, marketing, and sales.\n*   **Helpful Experiences:** Internships in business development, marketing, or sales roles; leadership roles in student organizations; projects involving market research or business planning.\n\n**4. Consulting Roles:**\n\n*   **Common roles:** Business Analyst, Management Consultant (entry-level).\n*   **Relevant Skills:** Analytical skills, problem-solving, communication, presentation skills, understanding of business operations.\n*   **Helpful Experiences:** Case study competitions, consulting internships, projects involving data analysis and problem-solving.\n\n**To give you more specific advice, tell me about:**\n\n*   **Any internships or work experience you''ve had:** What were your responsibilities and what did you learn?\n*   **Specific skills you''ve developed:** Are you particularly good at financial modeling, data analysis, communication, or something else?\n*   **Areas of interest within business:** Are you passionate about finance, marketing, management, or something else?\n*   **What kind of role are you looking for (entry-level, internship etc.)**\n\nOnce I have this information, I can give you more tailored recommendations! For example, I can suggest specific courses or certifications to boost your skills, or point you towards companies that are a good fit for your interests. Let''s work together to find the right path for you, Gokul!\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T07:28:53.745Z"}]', '2026-01-29 07:28:53.786428+00', '2026-01-29 07:28:53.786428+00'),
	('47bff846-d5d8-4a75-90ef-ec3a8af7490c', '95364f0d-23fb-4616-b0f4-48caafee5439', 'hi', '[{"id": "bf5f416c-27da-4541-a37a-0e869a7bc4db", "role": "user", "content": "hi", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T07:43:02.885Z"}, {"id": "74f32176-f90d-4e7d-9dbf-4ba489ef1314", "role": "assistant", "content": "Hi Gokul! I''m here to help you explore career options with your B.COM degree from PES University. I can provide personalized guidance and recommendations.\n\nTo get started, tell me, what are you most interested in exploring right now? Are you thinking about specific industries, types of roles, or further education? Or are you unsure and want to explore general options?\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T07:43:02.886Z"}, {"id": "376aa4d7-b04c-4235-88ec-b252782280ca", "role": "user", "content": "Help me prepare for upcoming interviews", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T08:17:57.630Z"}, {"id": "1256f52b-6cef-4be8-81d7-dbbaf198fa73", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay, Gokul, let''s get you prepped for those interviews! To give you the best advice, I need a little more information. Tell me:\n\n1.  **What kind of roles are these interviews for?** (e.g., Finance Intern, Accounting Associate, Marketing Assistant). Knowing the specific role will help me tailor the advice.\n2.  **What companies are you interviewing with?** (If you''re comfortable sharing). This helps me understand the company culture and expectations.\n3.  **What are you most nervous about in interviews?** (e.g., technical questions, behavioral questions, talking about weaknesses).\n\nIn the meantime, here''s some general advice that applies to most interviews for B.COM graduates:\n\n**I. General Interview Preparation:**\n\n*   **Research the Company:** Understand their mission, values, products/services, and recent news.\n*   **Review the Job Description:** Identify the key skills and experiences they''re looking for and prepare examples of how you meet those requirements.\n*   **Prepare for Common Interview Questions:**\n    *   \"Tell me about yourself.\" (Focus on your skills and experiences relevant to the role)\n    *   \"Why are you interested in this role/company?\" (Show genuine enthusiasm and connect your goals with the company''s mission)\n    *   \"What are your strengths and weaknesses?\" (Highlight strengths relevant to the job and frame weaknesses as areas for development)\n    *   \"Tell me about a time you faced a challenge and how you overcame it.\" (Use the STAR method: Situation, Task, Action, Result)\n    *   \"Where do you see yourself in 5 years?\" (Show ambition and alignment with the company''s growth)\n    *   \"Do you have any questions for me?\" (Prepare thoughtful questions to show your engagement)\n*   **Practice the STAR Method:** This is a great way to answer behavioral questions. Structure your answers by describing the **Situation**, the **Task** you had to complete, the **Action** you took, and the **Result** of your actions.\n*   **Practice, Practice, Practice:** Mock interviews with friends, family, or career services can help you feel more confident and comfortable.\n\n**II. Skills to Highlight (Relevant to B.COM):**\n\n*   **Technical Skills:** Accounting software (e.g., Tally, SAP), Microsoft Excel (proficiency in formulas, pivot tables), Financial modeling.\n*   **Soft Skills:** Communication, teamwork, problem-solving, analytical skills, attention to detail, time management.\n*   **Knowledge:** Strong understanding of accounting principles, financial statements, business concepts.\n\n**III. During the Interview:**\n\n*   **Dress Professionally:** First impressions matter.\n*   **Be Punctual:** Arrive on time (or a few minutes early for online interviews).\n*   **Maintain Eye Contact:** Show confidence and engagement.\n*   **Listen Carefully:** Pay attention to the questions and answer them thoughtfully.\n*   **Be Enthusiastic:** Show your genuine interest in the role and the company.\n*   **Thank the Interviewer:** Express your gratitude for their time and reiterate your interest in the position.\n\n**IV. After the Interview:**\n\n*   **Send a Thank-You Note:** Within 24 hours, send a personalized thank-you email to the interviewer.\n*   **Follow Up:** If you haven''t heard back within the specified timeframe, follow up politely to inquire about the status of your application.\n\nOnce you provide me with more specific information about the roles and companies you''re interviewing for, I can give you more tailored advice! Good luck, Gokul! You''ve got this!\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T08:17:57.630Z"}, {"id": "3cd800be-8be9-44ff-acea-1db9657355b2", "role": "user", "content": "Accounting Associate", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T08:18:33.435Z"}, {"id": "2ed73206-4a12-41ca-9595-72ca6ccbaaeb", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay, Gokul, focusing on Accounting Associate roles will help narrow down the preparation. Here''s some specific advice tailored for those interviews:\n\n**I. Technical Skills Focus:**\n\n*   **Accounting Principles:** Be prepared to discuss your understanding of GAAP (Generally Accepted Accounting Principles) or IFRS (International Financial Reporting Standards), depending on the company''s practices. Review key concepts like accruals, depreciation, revenue recognition, and inventory valuation.\n*   **Financial Statements:** You should be very comfortable with the three main financial statements:\n    *   **Balance Sheet:** Assets, Liabilities, and Equity – understand the accounting equation (Assets = Liabilities + Equity).\n    *   **Income Statement:** Revenues, Expenses, and Net Income (or Loss).\n    *   **Cash Flow Statement:** Operating, Investing, and Financing activities.\n    *   Be prepared to explain how these statements are interconnected.\n*   **Accounting Software:** If the job description mentions specific software (Tally, SAP, QuickBooks, etc.), highlight your experience with it. If you don''t have direct experience, emphasize your ability to learn new software quickly. Mention any relevant coursework or certifications.\n*   **Excel Proficiency:** Essential for any accounting role. Be confident in using formulas (SUM, AVERAGE, VLOOKUP), pivot tables, and data analysis functions. Be prepared to describe situations where you used Excel to solve accounting-related problems.\n*   **Auditing Basics:** Understand the purpose of audits and different types of audits (internal, external). Be familiar with audit procedures and internal controls.\n\n**II. Common Accounting Associate Interview Questions:**\n\n*   **Technical Questions:**\n    *   \"Explain the difference between debit and credit.\"\n    *   \"How would you handle a situation where you found a discrepancy in a financial statement?\"\n    *   \"Describe the process of preparing a bank reconciliation.\"\n    *   \"What are the different methods of depreciation?\"\n    *   \"How do you ensure accuracy in your work?\"\n*   **Behavioral Questions:**\n    *   \"Tell me about a time you had to work with a tight deadline.\"\n    *   \"Describe a situation where you had to explain a complex accounting concept to someone with no financial background.\"\n    *   \"Tell me about a time you identified and resolved an error in your work.\"\n    *   \"How do you stay organized and manage multiple tasks?\"\n*   **Situation-Based Questions:**\n    *   \"What would you do if you were asked to do something that you felt was unethical?\"\n    *   \"How would you handle a disagreement with a colleague about an accounting treatment?\"\n\n**III. Questions to Ask the Interviewer (Examples):**\n\n*   \"What are the biggest challenges facing the accounting department right now?\"\n*   \"What opportunities are there for professional development and training within the company?\"\n*   \"What are the company''s long-term goals and how does the accounting department contribute to those goals?\"\n*   \"Could you describe the team dynamics and work environment?\"\n*   \"What are the performance expectations for this role in the first 3-6 months?\"\n\n**IV. Tailoring Your Resume and Cover Letter:**\n\n*   **Highlight Relevant Coursework:** Emphasize accounting, finance, auditing, and taxation courses.\n*   **Quantify Your Achievements:** Use numbers to demonstrate your accomplishments (e.g., \"Reduced processing time by 15% by implementing a new Excel macro\").\n*   **Use Keywords:** Incorporate keywords from the job description into your resume and cover letter.\n\n**V. Additional Resources:**\n\n*   **AccountingCoach:** Offers free and paid resources for learning accounting principles.\n*   **Investopedia:** A comprehensive online resource for financial and accounting definitions and explanations.\n*   **Practice Mock Interviews:** Focus on both technical and behavioral questions.\n\n**Key Takeaways for Accounting Associate Interviews:**\n\n*   **Accuracy and Attention to Detail:** Emphasize your commitment to accuracy and your ability to identify and correct errors.\n*   **Problem-Solving Skills:** Highlight your ability to analyze financial data and solve accounting-related problems.\n*   **Communication Skills:** Demonstrate your ability to communicate complex information clearly and concisely.\n*   **Ethical Conduct:** Emphasize your commitment to ethical principles and your understanding of accounting standards.\n\nGood luck with your interviews, Gokul! Remember to be confident, enthusiastic, and prepared. Let me know if you have any more questions! What are some specific companies you are interviewing for? Knowing the company will let me tailor the advice even further.\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T08:18:33.435Z"}, {"id": "08f242fb-6285-4592-b58e-6e45174c7504", "role": "user", "content": "google", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T08:19:10.726Z"}, {"id": "c49e234b-2bc5-48cd-b4d2-78cc7b6e24bd", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay, Gokul, interviewing with Google for an Accounting Associate role is a fantastic opportunity! Google is known for its innovative culture and high standards. Here''s some tailored advice to help you prepare:\n\n**I. Understanding Google''s Culture and Values:**\n\n*   **Google''s Mission:** \"To organize the world''s information and make it universally accessible and useful.\" Understand how the accounting function supports this mission.\n*   **Google''s Values:** Google emphasizes innovation, collaboration, data-driven decision-making, and a user-centric approach. Research their core values and think about how your skills and experiences align with them.\n*   **Google''s Accounting Practices:** Research if Google uses specific accounting software or systems. They likely use very sophisticated systems. Even if you haven''t used their exact systems, showing an interest and aptitude for learning them will be beneficial.\n\n**II. Specific Skills and Knowledge to Highlight:**\n\n*   **Data Analysis and Interpretation:** Google is a data-driven company. Be prepared to discuss your experience with analyzing financial data, identifying trends, and providing insights. Highlight your Excel skills, especially your ability to work with large datasets and create meaningful reports.\n*   **Process Improvement:** Google is always looking for ways to improve efficiency and effectiveness. Be prepared to discuss your experience with identifying and implementing process improvements.\n*   **Technical Proficiency:** While you may not be expected to be a coding expert, demonstrating an understanding of technology and its impact on accounting is important. If you have any experience with data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI) or programming languages (e.g., Python, SQL), be sure to highlight it.\n*   **Adaptability and Learning Agility:** Google is a fast-paced environment. Emphasize your ability to learn new things quickly and adapt to changing priorities.\n\n**III. Google-Specific Interview Questions:**\n\n*   **Behavioral Questions:** Google is known for its behavioral interview questions, which are designed to assess your problem-solving skills, leadership potential, and cultural fit. Be prepared to answer questions like:\n    *   \"Tell me about a time you had to solve a complex problem with limited information.\"\n    *   \"Describe a time you took initiative and went above and beyond what was expected of you.\"\n    *   \"Tell me about a time you had to work with a difficult team member.\"\n    *   \"How do you handle ambiguity and uncertainty?\"\n*   **\"Googleyness\" Questions:** Google looks for candidates who embody its values. Be prepared to answer questions that assess your creativity, curiosity, and passion for innovation. Examples include:\n    *   \"What are you passionate about outside of work?\"\n    *   \"What''s the most innovative thing you''ve ever done?\"\n    *   \"If you could solve any problem in the world, what would it be?\"\n*   **Technical Questions:** Expect questions that assess your understanding of accounting principles and your ability to apply them in real-world situations. The difficulty might be higher than for smaller companies.\n    *   \"How would you handle a situation where you identified a potential fraud?\"\n    *   \"Walk me through the process of preparing a consolidated financial statement.\"\n    *   \"How do you ensure compliance with accounting regulations and internal controls?\"\n\n**IV. Preparing for the Interview Process:**\n\n*   **Research the Interviewers:** Try to find out who will be interviewing you and research their backgrounds on LinkedIn. This can help you tailor your questions and demonstrate your interest in their work.\n*   **Practice Your Communication Skills:** Google values clear and concise communication. Practice explaining complex accounting concepts in a way that is easy for non-financial professionals to understand.\n*   **Prepare Thoughtful Questions:** Asking insightful questions shows that you are engaged and curious. Some examples include:\n    *   \"What are the biggest challenges and opportunities facing Google''s accounting team in the next year?\"\n    *   \"How does Google foster innovation within its accounting department?\"\n    *   \"What are the opportunities for career growth and development within Google''s finance organization?\"\n*   **Be Prepared for a Multi-Stage Interview Process:** Google typically has a rigorous interview process that may involve multiple rounds of interviews with different team members. Be patient and persistent throughout the process.\n\n**V. Key Takeaways for Google:**\n\n*   **Show Intellectual Horsepower:** Demonstrate your ability to think critically, solve problems, and learn new things quickly.\n*   **Demonstrate Leadership Potential:** Show that you are a self-starter who is willing to take initiative and lead others.\n*   **Embrace Google''s Culture:** Show that you understand and appreciate Google''s values and that you would be a good fit for their culture.\n*   **Be Prepared for Ambiguity:** Google is a fast-paced and constantly evolving company. Be prepared to handle ambiguity and uncertainty.\n\n**VI. Resources:**\n\n*   **Google Careers Website:** Explore the website for information about Google''s culture, values, and career opportunities.\n*   **Glassdoor:** Research Google''s interview process and read reviews from past candidates.\n*   **LinkedIn:** Connect with Google employees and learn about their experiences.\n\nLanding an Accounting Associate role at Google is competitive, Gokul, but with thorough preparation and a strong understanding of Google''s culture and values, you can increase your chances of success. Good luck! What aspects of the interview process are you most concerned about? Perhaps we can work through those concerns.\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T08:19:10.726Z"}]', '2026-01-29 07:43:03.006949+00', '2026-01-29 08:19:10.726+00'),
	('cac8afa0-afe0-496d-bb8f-66044a7536b1', '95364f0d-23fb-4616-b0f4-48caafee5439', 'Create a learning roadmap for my career goals', '[{"id": "536fac8d-883a-4384-89cd-1ff742d4267a", "role": "user", "content": "Create a learning roadmap for my career goals", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T08:41:29.706Z"}, {"id": "4e6c3bc7-68e1-414e-8445-cbc6703b1c7b", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay Gokul, to create a learning roadmap, let''s first define your career goals. Since you''re studying B.Com at PES University, some common paths include:\n\n*   **Finance:** Roles like Financial Analyst, Accountant, or Investment Banker.\n*   **Accounting:** Pursuing a CPA or becoming a Management Accountant.\n*   **Marketing/Sales:** Focusing on business development within a company.\n*   **Entrepreneurship:** Starting your own business.\n\n**To give you the best roadmap, please tell me:**\n\n1.  **Which of these (or any other) career paths interests you the most right now?**\n2.  **What are your current skills and experiences (including any internships, projects, or extracurricular activities)?**\n3.  **What is your timeline?** (e.g., \"I want to be ready for an internship next summer\" or \"I want to have a full-time job lined up after graduation.\")\n\nOnce I have this information, I can create a more specific and helpful learning roadmap for you!\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T08:41:29.706Z"}]', '2026-01-29 08:41:29.749378+00', '2026-01-29 08:41:29.749378+00'),
	('9680eca1-dc9a-4ad1-8284-47e0029329b0', '95364f0d-23fb-4616-b0f4-48caafee5439', 'whats my career options', '[{"id": "0c27d64a-b53a-4e09-a4e7-7e8543b46ea3", "role": "user", "content": "whats my career options", "timestamp": "2026-01-30T23:08:44.362Z"}, {"id": "8b11ab46-62bf-472d-a10a-d927acae2451", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay Gokul, let''s explore some career options with a B.Com degree from PES University! A Bachelor of Commerce opens doors to a wide array of possibilities. To give you the *most* relevant advice, let''s break this down into a few key areas:\n\n**Core Areas Directly Related to Your Degree:**\n\n*   **Accounting & Finance:** This is a popular and solid choice.\n    *   **Roles:** Accountant (various types), Financial Analyst, Auditor (Internal or External), Tax Consultant, Investment Banker (may require further qualifications).\n    *   **Why it''s a good fit:** Your B.Com provides a strong foundation in accounting principles, financial statements, and business law – all essential for these roles.\n    *   **Skills to Emphasize/Develop:** Financial modeling, data analysis, attention to detail, knowledge of accounting software (like SAP, Tally, or QuickBooks).\n    *   **Possible Next Steps:** Look into certifications like CA (Chartered Accountancy - India), ACCA (Association of Chartered Certified Accountants - UK), or CFA (Chartered Financial Analyst - US). Internships in accounting firms or finance departments are invaluable.\n\n*   **Banking & Insurance:** A stable and growing sector.\n    *   **Roles:** Bank Teller, Loan Officer, Insurance Underwriter, Financial Advisor, Investment Manager.\n    *   **Why it''s a good fit:** Your B.Com curriculum likely covers banking operations, insurance principles, and investment basics.\n    *   **Skills to Emphasize/Develop:** Customer service, sales, communication (written and verbal), risk assessment, knowledge of financial products.\n    *   **Possible Next Steps:** Explore internships at banks or insurance companies. Consider certifications related to specific financial products (e.g., mutual funds, insurance).\n\n*   **Business & Management:** Broader roles that leverage your business acumen.\n    *   **Roles:** Business Analyst, Management Trainee, Operations Manager, Sales Manager, Marketing Executive, Human Resources (HR) Generalist.\n    *   **Why it''s a good fit:** A B.Com provides a good understanding of business operations, marketing principles, and organizational structure.\n    *   **Skills to Emphasize/Develop:** Leadership, teamwork, problem-solving, communication, analytical skills, project management.\n    *   **Possible Next Steps:** Look for internships in various departments of companies. Consider an MBA (Master of Business Administration) later in your career to accelerate your growth.\n\n**Other Potential Avenues (May Require Additional Skills/Training):**\n\n*   **Entrepreneurship:** Starting your own business.\n    *   **Why it''s a good fit:** Your B.Com provides a solid understanding of business fundamentals.\n    *   **Skills to Emphasize/Develop:** Networking, leadership, self-discipline, sales, financial management.\n*   **Government Jobs:** Many opportunities in public sector banks, government departments, and regulatory bodies.\n    *   **Why it''s a good fit:** A B.Com is often a minimum requirement for many entry-level government positions.\n    *   **Possible Next Steps:** Prepare for relevant competitive exams (e.g., IBPS for banking, SSC for other government jobs).\n\n**To help me narrow down the *best* options for you, Gokul, tell me:**\n\n1.  **What subjects did you enjoy most in your B.Com program?**\n2.  **What are your strongest skills?** (e.g., are you good with numbers, communication, problem-solving, or something else?)\n3.  **What kind of work environment do you prefer?** (e.g., fast-paced, analytical, people-oriented, creative?)\n4.  **Are you interested in pursuing further studies or certifications?**\n\nOnce I have this information, I can provide more tailored advice. Good luck!\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-30T23:08:44.362Z"}, {"id": "e027a1f8-5205-477b-b00d-fffbcb006192", "role": "user", "content": "did you consider my assessment results?", "timestamp": "2026-01-30T23:09:09.238Z"}, {"id": "f76c9eba-3767-4c27-9983-7b27ea297a69", "role": "assistant", "content": "You are absolutely right, Gokul! My apologies. I am still under development and learning to integrate all available information seamlessly. I need access to your SkillPassport assessment results to give you the *most* personalized and accurate career guidance.\n\n**Please provide me with a summary of your assessment results, or tell me where I can find them within the SkillPassport system.** Once I have that information, I will be able to:\n\n*   Align career suggestions with your demonstrated strengths and aptitudes.\n*   Identify areas where you might want to develop additional skills.\n*   Suggest specific roles and industries that are a good fit for your unique profile.\n\nI appreciate you pointing out my oversight! I am committed to providing you with the best possible career guidance.\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-30T23:09:09.238Z"}]', '2026-01-30 23:08:44.497278+00', '2026-01-30 23:09:09.238+00'),
	('0422ac69-d1b1-4c69-97e6-4940c270b035', 'c5d30a55-8d9a-46e6-b8d0-6accc0415c1c', 'What jobs match my skills and experience', '[{"id": "135c0b2c-b39a-487c-abc1-16cd8d1ba186", "role": "user", "content": "What jobs match my skills and experience?", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T11:51:12.945Z"}, {"id": "135c0b2c-b39a-487c-abc1-16cd8d1ba186", "role": "assistant", "content": "Hi litikesh! 👋 Let''s take a look at how your skills and experience align with potential job opportunities.\n\n**Your Profile Highlights:**\n- **Field:** Master of Technology in Computer Science\n- **Key Skills:** Programming, SQL, ReactJs, Java, Teamwork, and Leadership Development.\n\n**Top Matches:**\n\n1. **Senior Full Stack Developer at Tech Corp Inc.** \n   - **Match:** 85%\n   - **Why it fits:** Your programming skills and experience with ReactJs and Java are highly relevant.\n   - **Skills Gap:** None identified; great fit!\n\n2. **Blockchain Developer Intern at CryptoVentures Labs**\n   - **Match:** 80%\n   - **Why it fits:** Your knowledge in programming and innovation aligns well with blockchain technologies.\n   - **Skills Gap:** Familiarity with blockchain-specific languages could enhance your fit.\n\n3. **Data Analyst Intern at InsightHub Analytics**\n   - **Match:** 75%\n   - **Why it fits:** Your SQL and data analysis skills are a strong match for this role.\n   - **Skills Gap:** Further experience in data visualization tools like Tableau would be beneficial.\n\nWould you like more details on any of these positions, or should I filter by location or job type? 😊", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T11:51:18.816Z"}]', '2026-01-29 11:51:18.875823+00', '2026-01-29 11:51:18.875823+00'),
	('9280017a-8fb5-4e16-b611-49556a960acf', '95364f0d-23fb-4616-b0f4-48caafee5439', 'What jobs match my skills and experience?', '[{"id": "61327cd7-042b-4ed5-a82a-813b7de810de", "role": "user", "content": "What jobs match my skills and experience?", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T11:50:48.024Z"}, {"id": "2eb6f132-07c9-48aa-b8c2-0d4b309b7657", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay Gokul, since you''re studying B.COM at PES University, there are a lot of career paths that could be a great fit! Many B.COM graduates find success in roles that involve finance, accounting, management, and economics.\n\nTo give you the *best* recommendations, I need a little more information about your specific skills and experiences. Could you tell me about any of the following:\n\n*   **Specific skills:** Are you strong in accounting software (like Tally or SAP)? Do you have excellent communication or presentation skills? Are you proficient in data analysis or financial modeling?\n*   **Internships/Projects:** Have you done any internships or projects related to finance, accounting, or business? What were your roles and responsibilities?\n*   **Areas of Interest:** Within the realm of business, what are you most passionate about? (e.g., finance, marketing, entrepreneurship, data?)\n\nIn the meantime, here are some *potential* job roles that are often a good fit for B.COM graduates:\n\n*   **Accountant:** Managing financial records, preparing taxes, and ensuring compliance.\n*   **Financial Analyst:** Analyzing financial data, providing investment recommendations, and managing risk.\n*   **Business Development Associate:** Identifying and pursuing new business opportunities, building relationships with clients, and negotiating deals.\n*   **Marketing Associate:** Assisting in the development and implementation of marketing campaigns, conducting market research, and analyzing marketing data.\n*   **Banking Associate:** Working in various roles within a bank, such as customer service, sales, or operations.\n\nOnce you provide me with more details about your skills and experience, I can give you more tailored and relevant recommendations! Let''s work together to find the perfect path for you, Gokul!\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T11:50:48.024Z"}, {"id": "c86530eb-f1d5-4907-9639-98f4619fb013", "role": "user", "content": "hi", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T11:52:22.935Z"}, {"id": "3178cdd4-c3ec-43a4-b454-d242b63e780e", "role": "assistant", "content": "Hi Gokul! How can I help you today? Are you ready to delve deeper into those career options we discussed, or is there something else on your mind? Let me know!\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T11:52:22.935Z"}]', '2026-01-29 11:50:48.059691+00', '2026-01-29 11:52:22.935+00'),
	('b2687239-eb89-4dbd-a0c2-af3275a72777', '95364f0d-23fb-4616-b0f4-48caafee5439', 'What jobs match my skills and experience?', '[{"id": "0bc0d646-3abb-46ad-9e2e-2b12b2badc1a", "role": "user", "content": "What jobs match my skills and experience?", "timestamp": "2026-01-30T12:38:33.958Z"}, {"id": "f6733279-aaa7-4450-99ce-4338025d1bf9", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay Gokul, since you''re studying B.COM at PES University, there are several career paths that could be a good fit for you. Let''s explore some options that typically align well with a B.COM degree:\n\n**Core Business Roles:**\n\n*   **Accountant:** This is a classic B.COM path. You''d be responsible for preparing and analyzing financial records.\n*   **Financial Analyst:** You could analyze financial data, provide forecasts, and help companies make investment decisions.\n*   **Business Analyst:** You''d work to improve business processes and systems by identifying problems and recommending solutions.\n*   **Auditor:** You could work internally or externally to examine financial records and ensure compliance.\n\n**Other Potential Paths:**\n\n*   **Banking:** Roles in retail banking, investment banking, or corporate finance.\n*   **Marketing:** While not always a direct path, your business knowledge could be valuable in marketing roles, especially those involving data analysis or financial aspects.\n*   **Human Resources:** Your understanding of business principles could be beneficial in HR roles.\n*   **Entrepreneurship:** Your B.COM provides a solid foundation for starting your own business.\n\n**To figure out which of these aligns best with you, consider these questions:**\n\n*   **What subjects in your B.COM program do you enjoy the most?** (Accounting, Finance, Economics, etc.)\n*   **What are you naturally good at?** (Analyzing data, communicating, problem-solving, etc.)\n*   **What kind of work environment do you prefer?** (Working independently, as part of a team, in a fast-paced environment, etc.)\n\n**Next Steps:**\n\n1.  **Reflect on your interests and skills:** Make a list of what you enjoy and what you''re good at.\n2.  **Research specific roles:** Use websites like LinkedIn, Glassdoor, and Indeed to research job descriptions and required skills for the roles that interest you. Look at entry-level positions.\n3.  **Network:** Talk to professors, alumni, and professionals in your field of interest to learn more about their experiences and get advice. PES University likely has an alumni network you can tap into.\n4.  **Consider internships:** Internships are a great way to gain experience and figure out what you like.\n\nLet me know what areas sound most interesting to you, and we can dive deeper into specific skills, courses, or opportunities!\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-30T12:38:33.958Z"}]', '2026-01-30 12:38:33.990558+00', '2026-01-30 12:38:33.990558+00'),
	('0da627b3-3ad0-4536-a516-eef75e1e8c85', '95364f0d-23fb-4616-b0f4-48caafee5439', 'hi', '[{"id": "1f9117cc-e74b-4f32-9c93-81357cb22063", "role": "user", "content": "hi", "timestamp": "2026-01-30T23:55:09.257Z"}, {"id": "6b07f50f-65df-44a6-8294-441777d4d0e6", "role": "assistant", "content": "Hi Gokul! I''m here to help you explore career options with your B.COM degree from PES University. I understand that choosing a career path can be exciting and maybe a little overwhelming. Let''s work together to find some great opportunities for you.\n\nTo start, what are some of your interests or skills that you enjoy using? Are there any particular subjects in your B.COM program that you find most interesting?\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-30T23:55:09.257Z"}]', '2026-01-30 23:55:09.309857+00', '2026-01-30 23:55:09.309857+00'),
	('9d43b4c1-59d0-4385-8a9d-2727c5a2a1da', 'ab46b2ac-9922-4569-adc6-73eb6b645202', 'What jobs match my skills and experience?', '[{"id": "9f3fe97f-9209-46d6-8fd8-8cb3bb215ee3", "role": "user", "content": "What jobs match my skills and experience?", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T04:06:44.279Z"}, {"id": "158a8e21-67c5-45cf-8eda-c00987a81261", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay, Meera, to give you the best possible recommendations, I need a little more information about your skills and experience! Since you''re studying for a Bachelor of Technology in Electronics, I can suggest some common career paths in that field, but knowing what you''ve already done will help narrow it down.\n\n**To help me understand your situation, could you tell me about:**\n\n*   **Any internships or projects you''ve worked on?** (Even small projects from your coursework are helpful!)\n*   **What specific areas of electronics are you most interested in?** (e.g., embedded systems, VLSI, communication systems, power electronics, etc.)\n*   **What are your strongest technical skills?** (e.g., programming languages like C/C++ or Python, specific software or hardware tools, circuit design, etc.)\n*   **What kind of work environment are you looking for?** (e.g., research and development, manufacturing, field applications, etc.)\n\nIn the meantime, here are some **potential job roles for electronics graduates** like yourself:\n\n*   **Electronics Engineer:** Designing, developing, testing, and manufacturing electronic components and systems.\n*   **Embedded Systems Engineer:** Developing software and hardware for embedded systems in devices like mobile phones, appliances, and vehicles.\n*   **VLSI Design Engineer:** Designing and developing integrated circuits.\n*   **Communication Systems Engineer:** Working on the design, development, and maintenance of communication systems.\n*   **Power Electronics Engineer:** Designing and developing power electronic circuits and systems.\n*   **Robotics Engineer:** Designing, building, and programming robots for various applications.\n*   **Instrumentation Engineer:** Designing, installing, and maintaining instruments and control systems used in various industries.\n\nOnce I have a better understanding of your skills and experience, I can provide a more tailored list of job roles and suggest specific resources for you to explore!\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T04:06:44.279Z"}]', '2026-01-31 04:06:45.228307+00', '2026-01-31 04:06:45.228307+00'),
	('9143a836-9bfc-4b96-8fab-8fd6c94bb48c', 'ab46b2ac-9922-4569-adc6-73eb6b645202', 'Help me prepare for upcoming interviews', '[{"id": "c3e4fce6-d3ac-4c6b-b0d4-6519b789bd3f", "role": "user", "content": "Help me prepare for upcoming interviews", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T04:35:43.787Z"}, {"id": "2718dcba-581c-45a7-b448-f851015bbd34", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay, Meera, let''s get you prepped for those interviews! To give you the best advice, I need a little more information.  Could you tell me:\n\n1.  **What kind of roles are these interviews for?** (e.g., Software Engineer, Hardware Engineer, Data Analyst, specific company roles, etc.)\n2.  **What companies are you interviewing with?** (Knowing the company helps tailor advice)\n3.  **What is the interview format?** (Technical, behavioral, panel, etc.)\n\nIn the meantime, here''s a general framework to get you started:\n\n**I. Technical Preparation (Especially important given your B.Tech in Electronics):**\n\n*   **Review Fundamentals:**  Brush up on core electronics concepts: circuit analysis, digital logic, microcontrollers (if applicable), signal processing, and any other relevant topics from your coursework.\n*   **Practice Problems:** Work through practice problems related to the role.  Websites like LeetCode (for coding roles), and interview preparation sites often have electronics-related questions.\n*   **Projects:** Be prepared to discuss your projects in detail.  Highlight the challenges you faced, the solutions you implemented, and what you learned.  Quantify your achievements whenever possible (e.g., \"Improved system performance by X%\").\n*   **Company-Specific Research:** Understand the technologies the company uses and tailor your preparation accordingly.\n\n**II. Behavioral Preparation:**\n\n*   **STAR Method:**  Use the STAR method (Situation, Task, Action, Result) to structure your answers to behavioral questions. This helps you provide clear and concise examples.\n*   **Common Questions:** Prepare answers to common behavioral questions like:\n    *   \"Tell me about a time you failed.\"\n    *   \"Describe a challenging project and how you overcame it.\"\n    *   \"Why are you interested in this role/company?\"\n    *   \"What are your strengths and weaknesses?\"\n    *   \"Tell me about a time you worked in a team.\"\n*   **Practice:** Rehearse your answers out loud! This will help you feel more confident and articulate during the interview.\n\n**III. Company Research:**\n\n*   **Website & Products:** Thoroughly research the company''s website, products, services, and mission.\n*   **News & Articles:**  Read recent news articles and press releases about the company to stay up-to-date on their latest developments.\n*   **Glassdoor & LinkedIn:**  Check out Glassdoor for employee reviews and interview insights.  Use LinkedIn to research the interviewers (if possible) and understand their backgrounds.\n\n**IV. Logistics & Mindset:**\n\n*   **Dress Professionally:** Choose appropriate attire based on the company culture. When in doubt, business casual is a safe bet.\n*   **Prepare Questions:**  Prepare thoughtful questions to ask the interviewer. This shows your engagement and interest.  Examples: \"What are the biggest challenges facing the team right now?\" or \"What opportunities are there for professional development within the company?\"\n*   **Positive Attitude:**  Maintain a positive and enthusiastic attitude throughout the interview.  Smile, make eye contact, and be engaging.\n*   **Relax & Be Yourself:**  Remember to relax and be yourself!  The interviewers want to get to know you as a person, not just a resume.\n\n**Next Steps:**\n\n1.  **Provide me with the details requested above.** The more information you give me, the more tailored my advice can be.\n2.  **Start practicing!**  Even a little bit of practice each day can make a big difference.\n\nGood luck, Meera! You''ve got this! Let me know those details, and we''ll create a more specific plan.\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T04:35:43.787Z"}, {"id": "3d6b1f91-18c1-4009-9bad-82c0e4b83329", "role": "user", "content": "hi", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T04:36:00.845Z"}, {"id": "c32f010b-1152-4617-bb9a-d11d9e1a10ce", "role": "assistant", "content": "Hi Meera! How are you doing today? What can I help you with regarding your career exploration or interview preparation? Let me know what''s on your mind!\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T04:36:00.845Z"}]', '2026-01-31 04:35:44.810501+00', '2026-01-31 04:36:00.845+00'),
	('1bc9163d-918f-4bf3-a594-4c4821b825db', 'ab46b2ac-9922-4569-adc6-73eb6b645202', 'What jobs match my skills and experience?', '[{"id": "3a9edebc-32a1-423e-b264-ecea28489bbc", "role": "user", "content": "What jobs match my skills and experience?", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T04:25:50.499Z"}, {"id": "75f84272-deb0-4b7b-a709-277bdd520b99", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay, Meera, to give you the best possible recommendations, I need a little more information about your skills and experience. Could you tell me about:\n\n*   **Technical skills:** What programming languages, software, or hardware are you proficient in? (e.g., Python, C++, MATLAB, PCB design, etc.)\n*   **Electronics specializations:** Are you interested in VLSI, embedded systems, communication systems, power electronics, or something else?\n*   **Projects:** Can you describe any personal or academic projects you''ve worked on?\n*   **Internships/Work Experience:** Have you had any internships or part-time jobs? What were your responsibilities?\n*   **Soft Skills:** Are you a good communicator? Do you enjoy teamwork? Are you a problem-solver?\n\nIn the meantime, based on your B.Tech in Electronics, here are some common career paths to consider:\n\n*   **Electronics Engineer:** Design, develop, test, and manufacture electronic components and systems.\n*   **Embedded Systems Engineer:** Develop software and hardware for embedded systems in devices like smartphones, appliances, and vehicles.\n*   **VLSI Design Engineer:** Design and develop integrated circuits for various applications.\n*   **Communication Systems Engineer:** Work on designing and implementing communication systems, such as wireless networks and mobile communication.\n*   **Control Systems Engineer:** Design and implement control systems for various applications, such as robotics and automation.\n*   **Power Electronics Engineer:** Design and develop power electronic systems for efficient power conversion and control.\n\nOnce I have a better understanding of your specific skills and interests, I can provide more tailored suggestions!\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T04:25:50.499Z"}]', '2026-01-31 04:25:50.557315+00', '2026-01-31 04:25:50.557315+00'),
	('f3df537b-22aa-469c-8225-46e587d09ce9', 'ab46b2ac-9922-4569-adc6-73eb6b645202', 'Review my resume and suggest improvements', '[{"id": "4d9e32eb-4c46-4295-b277-0f828e9d615c", "role": "user", "content": "Review my resume and suggest improvements", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T04:46:55.239Z"}, {"id": "8c2fd5a3-a88e-4c83-8451-6d8905cf17b5", "role": "assistant", "content": "Okay, Meera, I''m happy to help you review your resume! To give you the best possible feedback, I need to see your resume. Please share the content of your resume with me.\n\nOnce I have that, I will focus on these key areas:\n\n*   **Clarity and Conciseness:** Is your resume easy to read and understand? Are you using clear and concise language?\n*   **Content and Relevance:** Does your resume highlight the skills and experiences most relevant to the types of jobs you''re likely to apply for with your B.Tech in Electronics?\n*   **Quantifiable Achievements:** Are you using numbers and data to demonstrate your accomplishments?\n*   **Formatting and Presentation:** Is your resume visually appealing and well-organized?\n*   **Keywords:** Does your resume include keywords that are commonly used in the electronics industry?\n\nI look forward to helping you create a resume that showcases your talents and gets you noticed! Just paste the text here when you''re ready.\n", "timestamp": "2026-01-31T04:46:55.239Z"}]', '2026-01-31 04:46:55.272766+00', '2026-01-31 04:46:55.272766+00');
